import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'])
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Engineers')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of engineers and the population in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['hurricanes'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes in each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['engineers'] = data['engineers'] * data['population']
    data = data.sort_values(by='engineers', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['engineers'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    plt.title('Average Number of Engineers per State', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Engineers'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['population'], data['hurricanes'], c=data['id'], cmap='viridis', label='States')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of hurricanes and the population in each state?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="States", loc="upper left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['population'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
